Sentencas: Solid oxide fuel cells (SOFC) can be operated with a variety of fuels.
Titulo: Carbon deposition on Ni/YSZ anodes exposed to CO/H2 feeds

Sentencas: In anode-supported SOFC, these fuels may decompose or react catalytically in the anode compartment resulting in mixtures that, in most cases, include high concentrations of H-2 and CO.
Titulo: Carbon deposition on Ni/YSZ anodes exposed to CO/H2 feeds

Sentencas: In this study, the formation of carbon from CO and H-2 mixtures on Ni/YSZ anodes at 1073 K has been investigated using electrochemical and carbon characterization techniques.
Titulo: Carbon deposition on Ni/YSZ anodes exposed to CO/H2 feeds

Sentencas: More carbon is deposited when Ni/YSZ anodes are exposed to CO/H-2 mixtures than to pure CO.
Titulo: Carbon deposition on Ni/YSZ anodes exposed to CO/H2 feeds

Sentencas: Polarization of the anodes reduced the amount of carbon deposited but the extent of the reduction depended on the gas composition.
Titulo: Carbon deposition on Ni/YSZ anodes exposed to CO/H2 feeds
